For the fixture problem,

Let's assume I have 2 fixtures; fixture 'A' and fixture 'B'. They both have `ParallelScope.Self`, as well as 3 different test fixture data passed in. I want one of the test methods, 'aa', in fixture 'A' to run the individual fixture data one at a time instead of all in parallel. I want the rest of the tests in fixture 'A' to still run as `ParallelScope.Self`. I would like the tests in fixture 'B' to be unaffected by anything done in fixture 'A'. This makes `NonParallelizable` a bad option for the test method 'aa', as fixture 'B' will be affected by this.
